HEADWORD: Gory
<hw>Gor"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Gore</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Covered with gore or clotted blood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou canst not say I did it; never shake⟦br⟧
Thy <qex>gory</qex> locks at me.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Bloody; murderous.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Gory</xex>
emulation.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gosainthan</ent>⟦br⟧
